Do you even #ab roll?

I think one of the 🔑 parts of this movement that most miss is the pull back. 

Before you drive the wheel out, vacuum in your core and hold it while you extend. As you pull the wheel back in, pull though your vacuum and keep it in that position throughout. Pull ALL the way to where the wheel is between your knees. At no time, should your back be arched. So if you feel low back pain while doing this, don’t roll out as far and work on your core engagement prior to the roll out.

Legit, this is the ONE core exercise that always has me feeling like I got kicked in the gut the next day 🤣🤣

4 weeks post show 🥳

Weight is finally starting to go up. I’ll do a body scan next week to make sure the increase is muscle vs BF. 

Feeling strong in the gym again and slowly getting back to the strength I had prior to competing. 

Just like the lean out, the reverse takes time. It takes a LOT of effort and it takes patience. 

A lot of comments I hear now is something along the lines of.. how does it feel to be able to eat again. 🤦🏻‍♀️ Um… huh? That’s not how this works. I still eat/train for my goals regardless of the lean out process.

I do give myself more grace on Saturdays, maybe a few 🍷 and you know… 🍔 🍟 but other than that.. It’s eating for the goals 💪

What’s a #workoutFinisher ?

How do I pick the finisher?

Why do I need a finisher?

A finisher by definition- involves quick, intense bursts of cardio and/or strength exercises and is performed at the end of your regular workout

This should be an exercise that you use every last bit of energy you have to preform. I like to target the muscles I just worked to really push them further then I pushed during my lifts.

Not every finisher needs to be high impact. This KB clean to press is low impact. Elevating my heart rate while burninggggg my shoulders out.

Double tap if you found this helpful! Pop any questions into the comments 💪
